Package: rsalad
Title: A mix of useful R functions that are good for you
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: "Dean Attali <daattali@gmail.com> [aut, cre]"
Description: This package provides a collection of useful R functions, that
    I've found myself reusing often.  While there isn't a common specific theme
    to all these functions, they are mostly either for manipulating data frames
    or improving ggplot2 plots.
URL: https://github.com/daattali/rsalad
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports:
    magrittr (>= 1.0.1)
Suggests:
    dplyr (>= 0.3.0),
    ggplot2 (>= 1.0.0),
    knitr (>= 1.7),
    microbenchmark (>= 1.4),
    nycflights13 (>= 0.1),
    testthat (>= 0.9.1)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
